reviews.review_text:
"lookin' around fo my shoes" The first set  shows some real promise as Jerry turns it  up nicely during Walkin' Blues. The Jack-a-Roe is exceptional as Jerry just attacks it. Desolation Row is excellent as well as Jerry is clear and bright. The rest of the set features a sweet Broken Arrow and LRR.
Music is  good  but a huge misstep by the  band. Not sure if it was Jerry or Bob. They end it strongly.

Set II looks great on paper and Jerry is loud but the band and Jerry makes some  missteps  during Help on the Way the transition into Slipknot is a train wreck but quickly Jerry recovers and offers  up a  good one with a nice jam.
The Franklin's is text book.
Saint is very strong and  Crazy Finger has  a few blemishes and the Corrina is not bad.
Post space is nothing out of the ordinary but the Good Lovin' is  good.
